oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Martha Elmore at Cumberland Mountain State Park
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Miss Martha Elmore of Crossville, Tenn., having a problem with her fishing line at the Cumberland Mountain State Park. Elmore is standing on a rock at the lake shore. She is waering a bathing suit and heels with the fishing rod in her right hand. There is a fishing boat and treeline in the background on the other side of the lake.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
